We, the underwritten Roman Catholic Prelates of Ireland ‚ having, on behalf of ourselves and absent brethren, already expressed our wants and wishes respecting clerical education, m the Minutes submitted to your revision and correction, take the liberty at present to explain some of them more particu- larly, in order to remove misapprehensions, which may furnish an occasion of perplexity or equivocation.

As the principle of our application to Parliament seems universally admitted, we shall confine ourselves to those parts only of the detail to which, as we hear, objections have been made.
